    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breakwaters comprising a mound of rubble, having a core of small rocks or rubble to provide the basic stability, with an outer covering of larger boulders, or armoring, to protect it from removal by the sea.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>由碎石堆成的防波堤，提供穩固基礎的核心由較小的岩石或礫石組成，外層則覆蓋較大的圓石或護板，以防遭海水沖移。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
